  "prompt": "What are some islands located in the Pacific Ocean?",
  "response": "The Pacific Ocean is home to many islands and island groups. Some of the most notable include:\n\n1. **Hawaii** (United States) - An archipelago consisting of 8 main islands, including Hawaii (the Big Island), Maui, Oahu, and Kauai.\n2. **Fiji** - An archipelago of more than 330 islands, with Viti Levu and Vanua Levu being the largest.\n3. **Tahiti** (French Polynesia) - The largest island in the Windward group of French Polynesia.\n4. **Samoa** - Comprised of the islands of Upolu and Savai'i, among others.\n5. **Guam** (United States) - An island in Micronesia, and an unincorporated US territory.\n6. **New Caledonia** - A special collectivity of France, consisting of the main island of Grande Terre and several smaller islands.\n7. **Solomon Islands** - A group of islands in Melanesia, including Guadalcanal and Malaita.\n8. **Vanuatu** - An archipelago consisting of around 82 islands.\n9. **Gal\u00e1pagos Islands** (Ecuador) - A group of volcanic islands renowned for their unique wildlife.\n10. **Palau** - An island country with approximately 340 islands, part of Micronesia.\n11. **Easter Island** (Chile) - Famous for its Moai statues, located in the southeastern Pacific Ocean.\n\nThese represent just a small fraction of the countless islands scattered throughout the vast Pacific Ocean.",
